typeDescription.name: org.healthnlp.deepphe.uima.types.Treatment
typeDescription.description: A processual entity whose completion is hypothesized (by a healthcare provider) to alleviate the signs and symptoms associated with a disorder.

typeDescription.name: org.healthnlp.deepphe.uima.types.DiseasePhenotype
typeDescription.description: A clinically abnormal phenotype that is characteristic of a single disease.

typeDescription.name: org.healthnlp.deepphe.uima.types.PatientSummary
typeDescription.description: A role which inheres in a person and is realized by the process of being under the care of a physician or health care provider.

typeDescription.name: org.healthnlp.deepphe.uima.types.TumorSequenceVariant
typeDescription.description: A non-exact copy of a sequence_feature or genome exhibiting one or more (somatic) sequence_alterations when compared to the individual’s germline sequence.

typeDescription.name: org.healthnlp.deepphe.uima.types.Tumor
typeDescription.description: An abnormal space occupying structure arising in any part of the body and resulting from an uncontrolled proliferation of cells.

typeDescription.name: org.healthnlp.deepphe.uima.types.ClinicalManifestationOfDisease
typeDescription.description: A manifestation of a disease that is detectable in a clinical history taking or physical examination.

typeDescription.name: org.healthnlp.deepphe.uima.types.CancerPhenotype
typeDescription.description: A clinically abnormal phenotype that is associated with a global quality(ies) of the disease.

typeDescription.name: org.healthnlp.deepphe.uima.types.MolecularManifestationOfDisease
typeDescription.description: A manifestation of a disease, measurable at the molecular level that is detectable through a

typeDescription.name: org.healthnlp.deepphe.uima.types.TumorPhenotype
typeDescription.description: A clinically abnormal phenotype that is associated with a quality (ies) of a specific tumor.

typeDescription.name: org.healthnlp.deepphe.uima.types.Outcome
typeDescription.description: A processual entity that is either the outcome of a disease course or a part of a disease course and has etiological relevance.

typeDescription.name: org.healthnlp.deepphe.uima.types.ManifestionOfDisease
typeDescription.description: A quality of a patient that is (a) a deviation from clinical normality that exists in virtue of the realization of a disease and (b) is observable.

typeDescription.name: org.healthnlp.deepphe.uima.types.Cancer
typeDescription.description: A disease of cellular proliferation that is malignant and primary, characterized by uncontrolled cellular proliferation, local cell invasion and metastasis. (DO)

typeDescription.name: org.healthnlp.deepphe.uima.types.GermlineSequenceVariant
typeDescription.description: A non-exact copy of a sequence_feature or genome exhibiting one or more sequence_alterations when compared to the reference genome.
